CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 31, 1945, pg. 13 reads: "Prelude To Easter - These charming maids, posed beside a majestic palm, are just what the doctor ordered to put you in the mood for the Easter Parade. Misses Ida Mae Mauney, in a trim taffeta striped suit (right), and Elaine Davis, in an alluring print, were [a]mong the models in the fashion review sponsored by Lambda Kappa Mu Sorority, at the Kay Boys Club, last week. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Elaine Davis, and Ida Mae Mauney wearing matching plaid hat and dress, posed with palm plant between them in Kay Boys Club for Lambda Kappa Mu fashion review
